## UI/UX Rules

> This file is generated for frontend projects only. If this project does not have a UI layer, remove this file.

### Design System

- All visual decisions must reference the project design system or component library
- Do not introduce one-off colors, font sizes, or spacing values — use design tokens
- CSS framework in use: **{{CSS_FRAMEWORK}}**
- When in doubt about a visual decision, prefer the least surprising option for the user

### Responsive Breakpoints

Define breakpoints here as the project establishes them. Default starting point:

| Breakpoint | Min width | Usage                        |
|------------|-----------|------------------------------|
| `sm`       | 640px     | Large phones, small tablets  |
| `md`       | 768px     | Tablets                      |
| `lg`       | 1024px    | Laptops                      |
| `xl`       | 1280px    | Desktops                     |
| `2xl`      | 1536px    | Large monitors               |

Update this table to match the project's actual breakpoints.

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

All UI work must meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA. Required practices:

- Sufficient color contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text and UI components
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-navigable and have visible focus indicators
- All images and icons must have meaningful `alt` text or be marked as decorative (`alt=""`)
- Form inputs must have associated `<label>` elements or `aria-label` attributes
- Dynamic content changes must be announced to screen readers via `aria-live` regions where appropriate
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<header>`) before reaching for `<div>`

### Animation and Motion

- All animations must respect the `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
- Provide a no-animation fallback for every animated component
- Avoid animations that flash or flicker — risk of triggering photosensitive conditions
- Keep animation durations short (150–300ms for UI transitions); reserve longer durations for deliberate emphasis

### Component Conventions

- One component per file
- Co-locate component styles with the component file when using CSS Modules or scoped styles
- Prop interfaces must be explicitly typed — no implicit `any` for event handlers or children
- Default to controlled components; document when an uncontrolled pattern is intentional
